text.tspan: Daily protein supply from animal and plant-based foods, World, 1961
Daily per capita protein supply is measured in grams per person per day. Protein of animal origin includes protein from all
meat commodities, eggs and dairy products, and fish & seafood.
Data source: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2023)
Note: The FAO apply a methodological change from the year 2010 onwards.
